Finance minister Tito Mboweni will deliver his 2021/22 budget speech this afternoon. But there are fears that he might increase taxes to raise money for COVID-19 vaccines. This during a time of poor economic growth. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Tax Law expert Thabo Legwaila says the government needs to fight corruption instead of increasing taxes. READ: WATCH: 2021 Budget: Tax relief or Burden? "The truth is that what needs to be done is to find the political will to fight corruption, we need that," he says. His comments come at a time when there are fears Finance Minister Tito Mboweni might increase taxes to raise money for COVID-19. Mboweni will deliver his budget speech on Wednesday. Watch the interview above for more from Law expert Thabo Legwaila